abstract: Dr. Larry Braunstein rented his office from the Trumps. Relatives say he was central to a diagnosis that got the 22-year-old Mr. Trump a medical exemption.
snippet: Dr. Larry Braunstein rented his office from the Trumps. Relatives say he was central to a diagnosis that got the 22-year-old Mr. Trump a medical exemption.
lead_paragraph: In the fall of 1968, Donald J. Trump received a timely diagnosis of bone spurs in his heels that led to his medical exemption from the military during Vietnam.

abstract: An off-season overhaul produces a playoff team in Seattle, and Pete Carroll could not be prouder.
snippet: An off-season overhaul produces a playoff team in Seattle, and Pete Carroll could not be prouder.
lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — In the last moments of a tense, tight game, as his team huddled to take a final snap and secure not just a win over the Kansas City Chiefs but a surprising spot in the playoffs, Pete Carroll prowled up and down the Seattle Seahawks’ sideline, shouting, hugging, high-fiving and pumping his right fist defiantly in the cold, wet air.

abstract: We asked our reporters, editors and critics to share some of their favorite lines of 2018 — the funny, the poetic, the astonishing and the surreal.
snippet: We asked our reporters, editors and critics to share some of their favorite lines of 2018 — the funny, the poetic, the astonishing and the surreal.
lead_paragraph: I have written many, many words for The New York Times over the past 20 years. About actual wars between Israel and the Gaza Strip, and about intellectual wars between creationists and scientists. About political campaigns and school shootings. About a small town in the Midwest that tried to ban lying, and a small hummus place in the Mideast that tried to promote peace.

abstract: The agency that oversees Voice of America and other government broadcasting has endured a series of recent scandals. Soon, a Trump appointee will take over.
snippet: The agency that oversees Voice of America and other government broadcasting has endured a series of recent scandals. Soon, a Trump appointee will take over.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The American government’s broadcast service to the world has a problem: It is becoming the news itself.

headline_main: Troubled by Lapses, Government’s Voice to the World Braces for New Trump Management
headline_print_headline: Troubled Vessel For U.S. Ideals Faces New Tilt

abstract: Donald Trump, Mitt Romney, Meg Whitman, Pete Wilson, and Dianne Feinstein are just a few of the public officials who have been forced to acknowledge that they employed undocumented immigrants.
snippet: Donald Trump, Mitt Romney, Meg Whitman, Pete Wilson, and Dianne Feinstein are just a few of the public officials who have been forced to acknowledge that they employed undocumented immigrants.
lead_paragraph: The news that a New Jersey golf course owned by President Trump, who has made border security and the fight to protect jobs for Americans a cornerstone of his presidency, had been employing undocumented immigrants as housekeepers was far from the first such revelation about a prominent public official.

abstract: For years, the president has denied that he had any business interests in Russia during the 2016 election. His former personal lawyer now says otherwise.
snippet: For years, the president has denied that he had any business interests in Russia during the 2016 election. His former personal lawyer now says otherwise.
lead_paragraph: On Thursday, after Michael D. Cohen revealed new information about the Trump Organization’s business dealings with Russia, President Trump called his former personal lawyer a liar.

abstract: Nearly a dozen incoming House freshmen served in previous presidential administrations. Seven from the Obama administration are determined to restore Mr. Obama’s legacy.
snippet: Nearly a dozen incoming House freshmen served in previous presidential administrations. Seven from the Obama administration are determined to restore Mr. Obama’s legacy.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Their previous jobs have taken them to the Oval Office, the Situation Room and the Senate floor. One met with a Saudi king and plotted strategy to fight the Islamic State. Another cracked down on human rights abuses in North Korea. Their Rolodexes are flush with former cabinet members and current Pentagon officials who are happy to take their calls.
